0 -14 Td
(POLICY STATEMENT) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(This policy defines how staff and contractors access fictional field devices, shared) Tj
0 -14 Td
(terminals, and handheld systems in a distributed operations environment. It balances uptime) Tj
0 -14 Td
(with traceability by requiring individual accountability, documented handoff, and a clear) Tj
0 -14 Td
(escalation path when normal access controls interfere with safe operations.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(DEFINITIONS) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Field device: any handheld scanner, forklift terminal, wall-mounted station, or service) Tj
0 -14 Td
(console used to perform operational work.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Shared terminal: a device used by more than one worker across a shift, where session handoff) Tj
0 -14 Td
(controls are required.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Emergency access event: a time-bounded use of elevated credentials to restore a blocked) Tj
0 -14 Td
(operation when normal access is unavailable.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Session owner: the person whose credentials are currently active on the device.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(REQUIREMENTS) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Each person must use individual credentials when the device supports named sign-in. Shared) Tj
0 -14 Td
(generic logins may be used only where the device architecture cannot support named accounts) Tj
0 -14 Td
(and where a compensating log exists.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Devices left unattended must be locked, docked, or signed out according to the local timeout) Tj
0 -14 Td
(standard.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Handoffs between shifts must include device count, battery or charger state, visible damage) Tj
0 -14 Td
(notes, and confirmation that the prior session is closed.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Emergency access events must be approved by the shift lead and recorded with start time, end) Tj
0 -14 Td
(time, reason, and follow-up review owner.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Any field device that stores cached work after sign-out must be included in the end-of-shift) Tj
0 -14 Td
(audit checklist.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(PROHIBITED PRACTICES) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Do not share named credentials verbally, by chat, or by leaving them written on the device,) Tj
0 -14 Td
(charger, or nearby workstation.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Do not bypass a lock screen by borrowing another worker's badge unless the event is recorded) Tj
ET
endstream
