1 0 0 1 54 738 Tm
(as an emergency access event.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Do not leave a session active on a forklift, packing station, or service cart during meal) Tj
0 -14 Td
(breaks or maintenance windows.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Do not continue using a device with suspected tampering, missing seals, or unexplained) Tj
0 -14 Td
(repeated login failures without escalation.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(EXCEPTIONS AND ESCALATION) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- If an operation cannot continue because a device is locked to a departed worker, notify the) Tj
0 -14 Td
(shift lead and service desk. The lead decides whether to wait for normal unlock, perform) Tj
0 -14 Td
(supervised emergency access, or move the work to a spare device.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- If repeated session failures affect multiple devices in one area, escalate as a possible) Tj
0 -14 Td
(infrastructure or identity-provider incident rather than handling each device separately.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- If a contractor requires temporary access beyond one shift, the sponsor manager must) Tj
0 -14 Td
(document the business reason and the expected end date before access is extended.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(OVERSIGHT AND ENFORCEMENT) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Supervisors should audit at least one shared device handoff per week and verify that) Tj
0 -14 Td
(recorded handoffs match physical device location and condition.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- The service desk should trend repeat emergency access events by site and by device family to) Tj
0 -14 Td
(identify training gaps or brittle login workflows.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Any unexplained mismatch between recorded session owner and observed user must be treated as) Tj
0 -14 Td
(a control failure until resolved.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(IMPLEMENTATION NOTES) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(Teams implementing this policy should translate the requirements into checklists, approval) Tj
0 -14 Td
(forms, and repository controls that are easy to audit. Local convenience does not override) Tj
0 -14 Td
(documented retention, redaction, or access requirements.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(Where two rules appear to conflict, the stricter public-release rule governs until the policy) Tj
0 -14 Td
(owner publishes a written exception or clarifying revision.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
ET
